<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25148b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25148b">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25148b"> 148(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> legit ut clericus</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[on benefit of clergy:]</font> If the ordinary said &ldquo;<mark>legit ut clericus</mark>&rdquo; &mdash; i.e. &ldquo;he reads like a clerk&rdquo; &mdash; the offender was only burnt in the hand, and then set free. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECSA1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECSA1"><cite title="source">The Story of the Alphabet</cite></a>, rev. ed. (1913) 22</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14097b" href="c14all.htm#c14097b">VI.C.14:097(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
